cast.overview: Mumbai, India, November 26, 2008. While several terrorists spread hatred and death through the city, others attack the Taj Mahal Palace Hotel. Both hotel staff and guests risk their lives, making unthinkable sacrifices to protect themselves and keep everyone safe while help arrives.
cast.title: Hotel Mumbai

details.biography: Tilda Cobham-Hervey is an Australian film, TV and theatre actress from Adelaide, South Australia, with a background in circus performing and physical theatre. In 2014 Cobham-Hervey made her film debut at the age of 19 in 52 Tuesdays, a critically-acclaimed independent film directed by Sophie Hyde. She appeared in Hotel Mumbai in 2019, and plays Helen Reddy in the new biopic, I am Woman.
details.name: Tilda Cobham-Hervey
